60.7	The_Magnificent_Seven	The Magnificent Seven	The Magnificent Seven is a 1960 American western film directed by John Sturges. It is a western-style remake based on Akira Kurosawa's 1954 Japanese film Seven Samurai. The film stars Yul Brynner, Steve McQueen, Charles Bronson, James Coburn, Robert Vaughn, Brad Dexter, and Horst Buchholz who play a group of seven American gunmen who are hired to protect a small agricultural village in Mexico from a group of marauding Mexican bandits. The film's musical score was composed by Elmer Bernstein.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f6/Magnificent_original.jpg/220px-Magnificent_original.jpg
